com.bigdata.rdf.graph

Interface IBinder<VS,ES,ST>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinderBase

    public interface IBinder<VS,ES,ST>
    An interface that may be used to extract variable bindings for the vertices visited by the algorithm.
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

    • Method Summary

      Methods

      int getIndex()
      The ordinal index of the variable that is bound by this IBinder.

    • Method Detail

      • getIndex

        int getIndex()
        The ordinal index of the variable that is bound by this IBinder. By convention, index ZERO is the vertex. Indices greater than ZERO are typically aspects of the state of the vertex.

      • bind

        List<org.openrdf.model.Value> bind(org.openrdf.model.ValueFactory vf,
                                 IGASState<VS,ES,ST> state,
                                 org.openrdf.model.Value u,
                                 IVariable<?>[] outVars,
                                 IBindingSet bs)
        New multi-binding strategy allows binders to bind multiple values to a given output variable (multiplying the number of solutions by the number of bindings).
        Parameters:
        vf - The ValueFactory used to create the return Value.
        state - The IGASState.
        u - The vertex.
        outVars - The array of output variables.
        bs - The current binding set. Can be used to conditionally bind values based on the current solution.
        Returns:
        The Value for that ordinal variable or null if there is no binding for that ordinal variable.
